fr.sorbonne_u.datacenterclient.tests

Class TestProject

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sorbonne_u.components.cvm.AbstractCVM
      • fr.sorbonne_u.datacenterclient.tests.TestProject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    fr.sorbonne_u.components.cvm.ComponentVirtualMachineI

    public class TestProject
extends fr.sorbonne_u.components.cvm.AbstractCVM
    The class TestProject this test case allows you to see all the features implemented during the project

    Description

    this first test case, is the case of general test of our project. we create 2 computers each contains 4 processors and 2 cores per processor. we chose this number of processors because we have 2 applications that each require 4 cores and 2 ApplicationVM in the Ring Network that require 4 cores. the rest of the cores will be used to add new ApplicationVM or add cores. we set the upperbound to 20 and the lowerbound 10 (Experimentally, the ideal values ​​of executions are between its two bounds). The control strategy in this test case is our basic strategy (control on frequency - cores control, ApplicationVM control)

    in this case it is difficult to see all the cases of control (more precisely the addition of the cores because during the allocation of the ApplicationVM we can not know if in the computer there are still cores or not)

    We can observe the frequency change, the addition of an ApplicationVM from RingNetwork, the addition of an applicationVM directly through AdmissionController (rare case) as well as the lower bound is quite small we can not observe all the cases of release of resources.

    We have proposed two other test cases that show more control during the release of resources the addition of cores

    Invariant 

     invariant              true

    Created on : Jan, 2018

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant, Salammbo
